{"cursor":"12373","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Taxobox\n| name = Mountain goat status = lc | status_system = IUCN3.1 status_ref =  Database entry includes a brief justification of why this species\n| is of least concern. image = Mountain_Goat_USFWS.jpg image_width = 290px\n| regnum = Animalia phylum = Chordata classis = Mammalia ordo = Artiodactyla\n| familia = Bovidae subfamilia = Caprinae genus = [[Oreamnos]] genus_authority =\n| Rafinesque, 1817 species = 'O. americanus' binomial = Oreamnos americanus\n| binomial_authority = (Blainville, 1816) range_map = Oreamnos americanus\n| distribution.svg range_map_width = range_map_caption =\n}}\n\nThe 'mountain goat' (Oreamnos americanus), also known as the 'Rocky Mountain\ngoat', is a large-hoofed mammal found only in North America. Despite its\nvernacular name, it is not a member of [[Capra (genus)|Capra]], the genus that\nincludes the wild goat, [[Capra aegagrus]], from which the domestic goat is\nderived. A subalpine to alpine species, it is a sure-footed climber commonly\nseen on cliffs and ice.\n","linknr":717,"url":"Mountain_goat","recorded":1362505563,"links":55,"instances":["genus"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Caprids","Fauna of the Rocky Mountains","Mammals of Canada","Mammals of the United States","Megafauna of North America","Monotypic mammal genera","Fauna of the Western United States|Rocky Mountains","Animals described in 1816"],"headings":["Classification","General appearance and characteristics","Range and habitat","Movement patterns","Diet","Life cycle and mating","Aggressive behavior","Wool","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Mountain_Goat_USFWS.jpg/290px-Mountain_Goat_USFWS.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Status_iucn3.1_LC.svg/220px-Status_iucn3.1_LC.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Oreamnos_americanus_distribution.svg/220px-Oreamnos_americanus_distribution.sv